## How to use Mantine Components with or without Tailwind

This repo use Mantine UI ^7 version, what is a component based library, this facilitate the contract btw the dev team.

But we added support to tailwind, adding to the tailwind config all mantine UI classes, using a prefix `mtn` like `p-mtn-md` so we can keep the UI uniform accross, divs or componets.

### When use pure component?

If the component has no need to extra ui modification or small modifications, use the plain component with ui pros.

```tsx
<Text fz="lg">
  warehouse.
</Text>
```


### When use mixed component?

If we need to use pseudo or conditinal, we can use tailwind to facilitate, instead to need to create a `module.css` file.
```tsx
<Text fz="lg" className="hover:text-mtn-blue-5">
  warehouse.
</Text>
```

### When use divs and no component
When you need to create a unique UI, that will be not reusable many times, you have freedom to be creative with tailwind classes.


